description: REQUIRED — first substantive reply lists active rules under "### Active project rules"
alwaysApply: true
---

# Active project rules block

On **first substantive reply** (new chat, fresh run, mode/topic change)—before plan, explanation, or code—print exactly:

```markdown
### Active project rules
- `<subfolder>/<rule-name>.mdc`
- `<subfolder>/<rule-name>.mdc`
- ...
```

- One bullet per active file under `.cursor/rules/ai-rules/`; skip `*.mdc.disabled`.
- Include @-mentioned rules and glob-scoped rules matching files/task.
- Repeat on new topic, mode change (plan / build / test / low token / role), or when asked which rules apply—skip trivial tool-only replies.
- One short acknowledgement (≤20 words) may precede the heading—nothing else above it.
